cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL. 

This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a series of refinements to the Hybrid Task Cascade (HTC) Network, which is a deep learning architecture commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). The paper also conducts ablation studies to evaluate the impact of the proposed refinements, which is a common practice in experimental research. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to cs.MM (multimedia) and cs.CL (computational linguistics), which often involve experimental evaluation of models and algorithms.
